DTSTART:20260727T150000Z
DTEND:20260727T153000Z
DTSTAMP:20260721T184000Z
UID:savethehives-fbpost-4@savethehives.org
CATEGORIES:SaveTheHives,Facebook
COLOR:purple
DESCRIPTION:POST 4 — The bigger why (research framing)\n\nPost text:\nHo
 ney bees have lost 30–50% of managed colonies most years since the mid-2
 000s. Most of the survivors only make it because of constant human interve
 ntion.\n\nThe colonies that make it on their own — no treatment\, no hel
 p — are living proof that natural resistance is possible. Finding and tr
 acking them is the whole point of SaveTheHives. Every pin on our map is a 
 lead worth following. savethehives.org\n\nImage: images/learn-hero.jpg (sa
 me bee-line/tree illustration set\, alternate crop — keeps visual consis
 tency with Post 2 without literally repeating it)\n\nAlt text: "Illustrati
 on of a honey bee in a wildflower meadow with a hollow tree in the distanc
 e."\n\nLink: keep the trailing URL as-is — no preview card will generate
  since a photo is attached.\n\nSuggested timing: week 2\, day 2–3\n\nNot
 e: the 30–50% loss-rate figure is a general\, widely-cited industry rang
 e\, not SaveTheHives-collected data — fine for casual Facebook use\, but
  add a source if this copy ever moves to a press pitch.\n\nFull copy in FA
 CEBOOK_STARTER_PACK.md §3.
LOCATION:facebook.com/savethehives
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
